# ICT01 PORTFOLIO <img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/oJsHJ7XCLpYDIWcNOl/giphy.gif" width="50">
> **_Compilation of programs made during Empowerment Technologies: IT for Professional Tracks (MATLAB) course_**

These are the first set of programs I made in my entire life——focused on learning the basics of programming: variables, conditionals, loops, and the like. The programs are divided into five categories, those made during the course outcomes (lessons) of the course; from one (1) to three (3), and the final project submitted——technically the first ever project made. 

The said [project](https://github.com/ketpadilla/ict01Portfolio/blob/master/finalProject/) is a calculator designed for trigonometric functions. It provides users the answers to the missing variable of these functions given they provided what is given. It also allows users to see the graphs of these functions.

This does **_NOT_** to provide solutions to the course's activities.
